Assuming the n harvesters powering the system are statistically independent, the optimal size of a specific harvester gi will be determined by 3 factors:
the power ratio of the generator with respect to the other n − 1 harvesters;
the magnitude of the average power output;
the stability of the power output over the entire period T.

For a generator gi the power ratio κ1 can be expressed as
