The third factor κ3 represents the degree of fluctuations of power output within a period of the system. It makes use of a continuous time standard deviation to quantize how much the generator’s power output changes, as expressed in Eq. 15:
15κ3=1+1T∫0Tpgiηgi(t)-1T∫0Tpgiηgi(t)dt2dt-2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
